		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />NES virus:  I bought a used willem programmer on eBay.  It seems to work well, but I've only used it three times since I don't have an EPROM eraser. (does anyone know of a cheap(not $100) or easy-to-build eraser?)
<br />
<br />drk421:  I would have used a 27C256 EPROM, but I had a pile of 32-pin 128KiB ones that weren't being used.
<br />
<br />I'm going to start on an AOROM or CNROM cart soon, but I'll need to order some parts first.  The local Radio Shack doesn't seem to carry 74161 (or anything other than octal flip-flops and BASIC stamps).

		

