		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>eprom eraser</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I put together the simplest eprom eraser I could think of. I ordered a UVC fluorescent tube from the aquarium store I go to and bought a cheap little fixture from the local hardware place. I think the bulb was $20 and the fixture was $10 (Canadian $). I just lean the EPROM's next to the bulb, wait 20 minutes and it works every time. On my bulb I can fit 10 EPROM's at a time (32 pin ones). I could put more in if I modified the fixture.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
